# Day 4 - Time Complexity Practice

## Q1

for i in range(n):
    print(i)

Answer: O(n)

---

## Q2

for i in range(n):
    for j in range(n):
        print(i, j)

Answer: O(n²)

---

## Q3

i = n

while i > 1:
    i //= 2

Answer: O(log n)

---

## Q4

for i in range(n):
    print(i)

for j in range(n):
    print(j)

Answer: O(n)

---

## Key Notes

- O(1) → Constant time
- O(n) → One loop
- O(n²) → Two nested loops
- O(n³) → Three nested loops
- O(log n) → Divide by 2 each iteration

## What I Learned Today

- Time complexity measures growth of operations as input size increases.
- Constants are ignored in Big O notation.
- The dominant term determines the final complexity.
